# 🔍 Pashudhan Suraksha Insurance — Full Project Bug & Issue Report

> **Analyzed:** Backend (Node.js/Express/MongoDB), AdminFrontend, AgentFrontend, CustomerFrontend
> **Date:** 2026-02-27
> **Scope:** Controllers, Models, Routes, Middleware, Services, Auth, Payment, Commissions

---

## 🔴 CRITICAL BUGS (Break Core Functionality)

---

### 1. [payment.controller.js](file:///d:/Reimvide/pashudhan%20shuraksha/Insurance-Website/Backend/controllers/payment.controller.js) — Undefined `payment` variable in webhook handler
**File:** [Backend/controllers/payment.controller.js](file:///d:/Reimvide/pashudhan%20shuraksha/Insurance-Website/Backend/controllers/payment.controller.js) — Line ~378

```javascript
// BUG: 'payment' is undefined — the in-scope variable is named 'paymentRecord'
const amountPaid = payment?.amount ? parseFloat(payment.amount) : null;
const policyLabel = policy?.policyNumber || payment.policyId?.toString(); // crash
```

**Impact:** The Razorpay webhook `payment.captured` event will **crash at runtime** when trying to send the payment confirmation email. `payment` is not in scope — `paymentRecord` is. Webhook-based fallback payment emails will never send.

**Fix:** Replace `payment` with `paymentRecord` on lines 378 and 382.

---

### 2. [agent.controller.js](file:///d:/Reimvide/pashudhan%20shuraksha/Insurance-Website/Backend/controllers/agent.controller.js) — [updateAgentProfile](file:///d:/Reimvide/pashudhan%20shuraksha/Insurance-Website/Backend/controllers/agent.controller.js#119-197) uses `agent.user` but populated field is `agent.userId`
**File:** [Backend/controllers/agent.controller.js](file:///d:/Reimvide/pashudhan%20shuraksha/Insurance-Website/Backend/controllers/agent.controller.js) — Lines 155–162

```javascript
// agent is populated with .populate('userId') — field is agent.userId, NOT agent.user
if (agent.user) {  // ALWAYS false; agent.user is undefined
    agent.user.fullName = fullName || agent.user.fullName;
    await agent.user.save({ session });
}
```

**Impact:** Updating an agent's user profile fields (fullName, phone, address, etc.) via `PUT /api/agents/profile` **never works**. The `agent.user` guard is always falsy.

**Fix:** Change all `agent.user` references to `agent.userId`.

---

### 3. [admin.route.js](file:///d:/Reimvide/pashudhan%20shuraksha/Insurance-Website/Backend/routes/admin.route.js) — Route conflict: `/policies/:id` shadows `/policies/:policyNumber/download`
**File:** [Backend/routes/admin.route.js](file:///d:/Reimvide/pashudhan%20shuraksha/Insurance-Website/Backend/routes/admin.route.js) — Lines 49–50

```javascript
router.get('/policies/:id', getPolicyDetails);
router.get('/policies/:policyNumber/download', downloadPolicyPDF); // unreachable!
```

**Impact:** Any GET to `/api/admin/policies/xxx/download` is matched by `:id` first and routed to [getPolicyDetails](file:///d:/Reimvide/pashudhan%20shuraksha/Insurance-Website/Backend/controllers/admin.controller.js#354-394). The download route is **effectively unreachable**.

**Fix:** Move the `/policies/:policyNumber/download` route BEFORE the [/:id](file:///d:/Reimvide/pashudhan%20shuraksha/Insurance-Website/CustomerFrontend/src/context/AuthContext.jsx#11-246) route.

---

### 4. Agent Code Generation — No uniqueness check in [agent.controller.js](file:///d:/Reimvide/pashudhan%20shuraksha/Insurance-Website/Backend/controllers/agent.controller.js)
**File:** [Backend/controllers/agent.controller.js](file:///d:/Reimvide/pashudhan%20shuraksha/Insurance-Website/Backend/controllers/agent.controller.js) — Lines 38–39

```javascript
const randomBytes = crypto.randomBytes(3).toString('hex').toUpperCase();
const agentCode = `AG${randomBytes}`;  // NOT checked for uniqueness!
```

**Impact:** The "upgrade to agent" flow generates agent codes without checking for collisions. Concurrent registrations can produce duplicate `agentCode` values causing `MongoServerError: duplicate key`. (Note: [auth.controller.js](file:///d:/Reimvide/pashudhan%20shuraksha/Insurance-Website/Backend/controllers/auth.controller.js) correctly uses [generateAgentCodeV2()](file:///d:/Reimvide/pashudhan%20shuraksha/Insurance-Website/Backend/controllers/auth.controller.js#73-87) with a uniqueness loop — but [agent.controller.js](file:///d:/Reimvide/pashudhan%20shuraksha/Insurance-Website/Backend/controllers/agent.controller.js) does not.)

---

### 5. [agentAddPolicy](file:///d:/Reimvide/pashudhan%20shuraksha/Insurance-Website/Backend/controllers/agent.controller.js#932-1082) — New customer created with no email verification or notification
**File:** [Backend/controllers/agent.controller.js](file:///d:/Reimvide/pashudhan%20shuraksha/Insurance-Website/Backend/controllers/agent.controller.js) — Lines 982–987

```javascript
const newUser = await User.create({
    ...customerData,
    role: 'customer',
    password: `PS@${customerData.phone.slice(-4)}`  // Weak default password
});
```

**Issues:**
- `emailVerified` defaults to `false` — customer **cannot log in** without OTP, but no OTP email is sent.
- No email notification/welcome message is sent to the newly created customer.
- Weak, predictable password is set as default.

