## 🟠 IMPORTANT BUGS (Functional Issues)

---

### 6. [payment.controller.js](file:///d:/Reimvide/pashudhan%20shuraksha/Insurance-Website/Backend/controllers/payment.controller.js) — `.populate('policy')` on a non-existent virtual in Payment model
**File:** [Backend/controllers/payment.controller.js](file:///d:/Reimvide/pashudhan%20shuraksha/Insurance-Website/Backend/controllers/payment.controller.js) — Line 277

```javascript
const payments = await Payment.find({ customerId: req.user._id })
    .populate('policy')  // 'policy' virtual does NOT exist on Payment model
    .sort({ createdAt: -1 });
```

**Impact:** Silently fails — returns `policy: null` for all payments. The Payment model has `policyId` (ref: Policy), not a `policy` virtual.

**Fix:** Change to `.populate('policyId')` or add a `policy` virtual to the Payment schema.

---

### 7. [claim.controller.js](file:///d:/Reimvide/pashudhan%20shuraksha/Insurance-Website/Backend/controllers/claim.controller.js) — Wrong populate paths (`policy`, `reviewer` instead of `policyId`, `reviewedBy`)
**File:** [Backend/controllers/claim.controller.js](file:///d:/Reimvide/pashudhan%20shuraksha/Insurance-Website/Backend/controllers/claim.controller.js) — Lines 92–93

```javascript
.populate({ path: 'policy', strictPopulate: false })     // should be 'policyId'
.populate({ path: 'reviewer', strictPopulate: false })   // should be 'reviewedBy'
```

**Impact:** Both populate calls return `null` even though the data exists. The `strictPopulate: false` silences the error but returns no data.

---

### 8. [payment.controller.js](file:///d:/Reimvide/pashudhan%20shuraksha/Insurance-Website/Backend/controllers/payment.controller.js) [handlePaymentFailed](file:///d:/Reimvide/pashudhan%20shuraksha/Insurance-Website/Backend/controllers/payment.controller.js#409-420) — Query will always return null

**File:** [Backend/controllers/payment.controller.js](file:///d:/Reimvide/pashudhan%20shuraksha/Insurance-Website/Backend/controllers/payment.controller.js) — Line 411

```javascript
const payment = await Payment.findOne({ razorpayPaymentId: paymentEntity.id });
```

When payment **fails**, `razorpayPaymentId` is never assigned to the record (it's only set on success). This always returns `null`, so failed payment statuses are **never updated** via webhook.

**Fix:** Query by `razorpayOrderId` instead: `Payment.findOne({ razorpayOrderId: paymentEntity.order_id })`.

---

### 9. [policy.controller.js](file:///d:/Reimvide/pashudhan%20shuraksha/Insurance-Website/Backend/controllers/policy.controller.js) — `policy.customerId.toString()` fails when customerId is populated
**File:** [Backend/controllers/policy.controller.js](file:///d:/Reimvide/pashudhan%20shuraksha/Insurance-Website/Backend/controllers/policy.controller.js) — Line 333

```javascript
// policy.populate('customerId') was called above — customerId is now a full document
const isOwner = policy.customerId.toString()  // returns '[object Object]'
```

**Fix:** Use `policy.customerId._id?.toString()` when the field may be populated.

---

### 10. [commission.util.js](file:///d:/Reimvide/pashudhan%20shuraksha/Insurance-Website/Backend/utils/commission.util.js) — Zero-amount commission records are still inserted
**File:** [Backend/utils/commission.util.js](file:///d:/Reimvide/pashudhan%20shuraksha/Insurance-Website/Backend/utils/commission.util.js) — Lines 53–64

When `sellerCommissionAmount = 0`, a commission record with `amount = 0` is still persisted. This clutters the commissions table and confuses admin dashboards.

**Fix:** Only push the seller commission record if `sellerCommissionAmount > 0`.

---

### 11. [auth.controller.js](file:///d:/Reimvide/pashudhan%20shuraksha/Insurance-Website/Backend/controllers/auth.controller.js) — [refreshSession](file:///d:/Reimvide/pashudhan%20shuraksha/Insurance-Website/Backend/controllers/auth.controller.js#713-753) validates `emailVerified` which may cause issues for valid agent sessions

**File:** [Backend/controllers/auth.controller.js](file:///d:/Reimvide/pashudhan%20shuraksha/Insurance-Website/Backend/controllers/auth.controller.js) — Line 731

```javascript
if (!user || user.status !== 'active' || !user.emailVerified) {
    return res.status(401).json({ success: false, message: 'User not allowed' });
}
```

Agents created via [agentAddPolicy](file:///d:/Reimvide/pashudhan%20shuraksha/Insurance-Website/Backend/controllers/agent.controller.js#932-1082) have `emailVerified: false`. A valid agent session refresh can silently fail for such users.

---

## 🟡 LOGIC & DESIGN ISSUES

---

### 12. Both access and refresh tokens use the same `JWT_SECRET`
**File:** [Backend/middleware/auth.middleware.js](file:///d:/Reimvide/pashudhan%20shuraksha/Insurance-Website/Backend/middleware/auth.middleware.js) — Lines 138–151

Using the same secret for both token types reduces security. Best practice is a separate `JWT_REFRESH_SECRET`.

---

### 13. OTP codes logged to console — security risk in production
**File:** [Backend/controllers/auth.controller.js](file:///d:/Reimvide/pashudhan%20shuraksha/Insurance-Website/Backend/controllers/auth.controller.js) — Line 44

```javascript
console.log(`Sending OTP to ${user.email} (Name: ${user.fullName}): ${otp}`);
```

OTP codes in server logs is a security vulnerability. Should be wrapped in `if (process.env.NODE_ENV === 'development')`.

---

### 14. `error.message` exposed in 500 API responses across all controllers

```javascript
res.status(500).json({ success: false, message: '...', error: error.message });
```

In production, `error.message` can leak database schema details, internal paths, or stack information.

---

### 15. [agent.controller.js](file:///d:/Reimvide/pashudhan%20shuraksha/Insurance-Website/Backend/controllers/agent.controller.js) [getAgentStats](file:///d:/Reimvide/pashudhan%20shuraksha/Insurance-Website/Backend/controllers/agent.controller.js#296-395) — `a.user` references non-existent field
**File:** [Backend/controllers/agent.controller.js](file:///d:/Reimvide/pashudhan%20shuraksha/Insurance-Website/Backend/controllers/agent.controller.js) — Line 370

```javascript
name: a.user?.fullName,  // 'a.user' is undefined; should be 'a.userId?.fullName'
```

All top performer names will be `undefined` on the agent dashboard.

---

### 16. [agent.controller.js](file:///d:/Reimvide/pashudhan%20shuraksha/Insurance-Website/Backend/controllers/agent.controller.js) [updateCustomerNotes](file:///d:/Reimvide/pashudhan%20shuraksha/Insurance-Website/Backend/controllers/agent.controller.js#753-790) — No null check on [agent](file:///d:/Reimvide/pashudhan%20shuraksha/Insurance-Website/Backend/controllers/agent.controller.js#932-1082)
**File:** [Backend/controllers/agent.controller.js](file:///d:/Reimvide/pashudhan%20shuraksha/Insurance-Website/Backend/controllers/agent.controller.js) — Lines 760–771

```javascript
const agent = await Agent.findOne({ userId: req.user._id });
// No null check! Next line crashes if agent is null:
const policy = await Policy.findOne({ agentId: agent._id, customerId: id });
```

---

### 17. [admin.controller.js](file:///d:/Reimvide/pashudhan%20shuraksha/Insurance-Website/Backend/controllers/admin.controller.js) [getAllAgents](file:///d:/Reimvide/pashudhan%20shuraksha/Insurance-Website/Backend/controllers/admin.controller.js#690-869) — Full collection loaded to memory for pagination
**File:** [Backend/controllers/admin.controller.js](file:///d:/Reimvide/pashudhan%20shuraksha/Insurance-Website/Backend/controllers/admin.controller.js) — Lines 749–753

```javascript
const allAgents = await baseQuery; // ALL agents in memory
const validAgents = allAgents.filter(a => a.userId);
```

This is a scalability issue. Should use MongoDB `$lookup` + `$match` aggregation instead.

---

### 18. Webhook signature verified against re-serialized JSON (not raw body)
**File:** [Backend/controllers/payment.controller.js](file:///d:/Reimvide/pashudhan%20shuraksha/Insurance-Website/Backend/controllers/payment.controller.js) — Line 304

```javascript
shasum.update(JSON.stringify(req.body)); // Re-serialized — may differ from original
```

Razorpay recommends verifying against the **raw request body**. JSON re-serialization can change property order and cause signature mismatches.

**Fix:** Use `express.raw()` for the webhook route to capture the raw body.

---

### 19. [verifyEmailOTP](file:///d:/Reimvide/pashudhan%20shuraksha/Insurance-Website/Backend/controllers/auth.controller.js#640-679) checks invalidity before expiry — reversed logic
**File:** [Backend/controllers/auth.controller.js](file:///d:/Reimvide/pashudhan%20shuraksha/Insurance-Website/Backend/controllers/auth.controller.js) — Lines 660–665

Expiry should be checked first. If OTP is expired, user should be told to request a new one rather than "Invalid OTP".

