## 🔵 MINOR / CODE QUALITY ISSUES

---

### 20. `razorpay` server-side Node.js SDK installed as frontend dependency (wrong package)
**Files:** [AgentFrontend/package.json](file:///d:/Reimvide/pashudhan%20shuraksha/Insurance-Website/AgentFrontend/package.json), [CustomerFrontend/package.json](file:///d:/Reimvide/pashudhan%20shuraksha/Insurance-Website/CustomerFrontend/package.json)

```json
"razorpay": "^2.9.6"
```

This is the server-side SDK. Frontend should use Razorpay Checkout.js via CDN `<script>` tag. The `window.Razorpay` constructor comes from the CDN script, not this npm package.

---

### 21. `isBrowser` variable declared but never used in both [api.service.js](file:///d:/Reimvide/pashudhan%20shuraksha/Insurance-Website/AgentFrontend/src/services/api.service.js) files
**Files:** [CustomerFrontend/src/services/api.service.js](file:///d:/Reimvide/pashudhan%20shuraksha/Insurance-Website/CustomerFrontend/src/services/api.service.js) L5, [AgentFrontend/src/services/api.service.js](file:///d:/Reimvide/pashudhan%20shuraksha/Insurance-Website/AgentFrontend/src/services/api.service.js) L5

```javascript
const isBrowser = typeof window !== 'undefined'; // dead variable
```

---

### 22. ESLint `no-unused-vars` errors found in all three frontends

- **AdminFrontend:** `username`, `password` unused
- **AgentFrontend:** ESLint exit code 1 (errors present)
- **CustomerFrontend:** `paymentId`, `signature` unused (in payment handler)

All three frontends fail `npm run lint` with exit code 1.

---

### 23. [auth.controller.js](file:///d:/Reimvide/pashudhan%20shuraksha/Insurance-Website/Backend/controllers/auth.controller.js) [register](file:///d:/Reimvide/pashudhan%20shuraksha/Insurance-Website/AgentFrontend/src/services/api.service.js#182-186) — Redundant ternary with hardcoded role
**File:** [Backend/controllers/auth.controller.js](file:///d:/Reimvide/pashudhan%20shuraksha/Insurance-Website/Backend/controllers/auth.controller.js) — Lines 122–124

```javascript
const targetRole = 'customer'; // hardcoded
emailVerified: targetRole === 'admin' ? true : false, // always false
otpCode: targetRole === 'admin' ? null : otp,          // always otp
```

Simplify to: `emailVerified: false, otpCode: otp`

---

### 24. Commented-out dead code block in [api.service.js](file:///d:/Reimvide/pashudhan%20shuraksha/Insurance-Website/AgentFrontend/src/services/api.service.js) (both Customer and Agent)
**File:** [api.service.js](file:///d:/Reimvide/pashudhan%20shuraksha/Insurance-Website/AgentFrontend/src/services/api.service.js) — Lines 340–353

A fully commented-out duplicate `contactAPI` block should be removed.

---

### 25. [forgotPassword](file:///d:/Reimvide/pashudhan%20shuraksha/Insurance-Website/Backend/controllers/auth.controller.js#551-597) saves reset token to DB before sending email — token is saved even if email fails
**File:** [Backend/controllers/auth.controller.js](file:///d:/Reimvide/pashudhan%20shuraksha/Insurance-Website/Backend/controllers/auth.controller.js) — Lines 566–587

If `sendEmail()` throws, the reset token is already in the DB but the email was never sent. User is stuck with a token they can't use. The token should only be saved if email succeeds, or the failure should be handled gracefully.

